## 5) Git commands on this Windows workspace

The user shell is PowerShell. When committing/pushing here, use PowerShell-safe git commands; do **not** use POSIX-only chaining or heredocs (`&&`, `cat <<'EOF'`, etc.).

Prefer separate commands:

```powershell
git add -- "path/to/file"
git commit -m "Short message."
git push
```

If multiple commands must be in one shell call, use PowerShell syntax (`;` plus `$LASTEXITCODE` checks), not Bash syntax.
